The paper deals with image analysis and machine learning techniques for digital pathology analysis. Specifically, it proposes a weakly supervised learning-based approach for evidence localization in pathology images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks for image classification and segmentation, which are common techniques in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with natural language processing techniques for clinical applications, which suggests that it may belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of medical images, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
